Proposed Endeavor:

I seek to advance the modernization of healthcare and financial analytics infrastructure in the United States through the development of scalable, compliant, and data-driven engineering frameworks. My work focuses on bridging data silos across state Medicaid programs, payer systems, and healthcare providers by implementing cloud-native architectures‚Äîleveraging tools such as AWS Glue, Snowflake, Databricks, and dbt‚Äîto ensure secure, auditable, and real-time decision-making. In parallel, I design pricing and revenue analytics models that enhance financial transparency and efficiency for both public and private organizations.

By integrating healthcare interoperability standards (FHIR/HL7) with financial analytics practices, my goal is to build open, reproducible data pipelines that improve policy-driven healthcare delivery and fiscal accountability. This endeavor aligns with national priorities in healthcare cost optimization, data governance, and digital modernization. Through continued publication, collaboration, and applied system development, I intend to contribute frameworks and case studies that strengthen U.S. leadership in data-driven public health and economic infrastructure.
